{
  "video_id": "a7MeCPfaPR0",
  "title": "TEDxBoulder - Andrew Currie - Protecting Endangered Species for Future Generations",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Denise RQ Reviewer: Lena Clemente"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14709.0,
      "end_time": 17750.0,
      "text": "I'm going to start with a quote by the Dalai Lama,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17752.0,
      "end_time": 19985.0,
      "text": "\"Today, more than ever before,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 19986.0,
      "end_time": 24453.0,
      "text": "life must be characterized by a sense of universal responsibility"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 24454.0,
      "end_time": 27869.0,
      "text": "not only nation to nation and human to human"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 27870.0,
      "end_time": 31134.0,
      "text": "but human to other forms of life.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 31135.0,
      "end_time": 32824.0,
      "text": "That's what I'm here to talk about;"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 32825.0,
      "end_time": 35220.0,
      "text": "I'm passionate about wildlife conservation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 35230.0,
      "end_time": 36812.0,
      "text": "thus, other forms of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36813.0,
      "end_time": 39392.0,
      "text": "In the last ten years, I've done everything I can"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 39393.0,
      "end_time": 41500.0,
      "text": "to learn as much as I can about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41501.0,
      "end_time": 44458.0,
      "text": "I've read books, I've talked to experts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44460.0,
      "end_time": 48650.0,
      "text": "I've gone to conferences, and traveled the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48660.0,
      "end_time": 52400.0,
      "text": "I wanted to see for myself what's going on in these places."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 52500.0,
      "end_time": 55953.0,
      "text": "I visited chimpanzees in Uganda,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 55954.0,
      "end_time": 60830.0,
      "text": "I visited mountain gorilla families in Rwanda."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 60840.0,
      "end_time": 65287.0,
      "text": "Everywhere I go, the root cause of the dwindling numbers of these species"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 65288.0,
      "end_time": 68213.0,
      "text": "is human population pressure."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 68214.0,
      "end_time": 72184.0,
      "text": "A recent visual example I saw of this is in Uganda,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72185.0,
      "end_time": 74790.0,
      "text": "with farms going up the hillside"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 74830.0,
      "end_time": 77125.0,
      "text": "right to the boundary of Bwindi National Park,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 77126.0,
      "end_time": 80920.0,
      "text": "part of the last remaining habitat for the mountain gorilla."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 80921.0,
      "end_time": 82801.0,
      "text": "Let's talk about population."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 82802.0,
      "end_time": 86510.0,
      "text": "We're at 6.7 billion people in the world today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 86520.0,
      "end_time": 90892.0,
      "text": "expected to rise to nine or ten billion just in the next 40 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90893.0,
      "end_time": 93780.0,
      "text": "The problem is we've already got a billion people"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 93781.0,
      "end_time": 96210.0,
      "text": "who don't have enough to eat."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96211.0,
      "end_time": 99977.0,
      "text": "What is it going to be like when we increase the pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 99978.0,
      "end_time": 101586.0,
      "text": "the human population pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101587.0,
      "end_time": 103722.0,
      "text": "by another 50%?"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 103723.0,
      "end_time": 108875.0,
      "text": "So, I think, what we are going to have are more conflicts, more wars"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 108876.0,
      "end_time": 110687.0,
      "text": "over scarcer resources,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 110688.0,
      "end_time": 112898.0,
      "text": "less drinking water per person."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112899.0,
      "end_time": 117270.0,
      "text": "We're going to have less food per person, more disease, and suffering."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 117271.0,
      "end_time": 120959.0,
      "text": "It's difficult to comprehend, but that's suffering on a global scale"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 120960.0,
      "end_time": 123211.0,
      "text": "when we are talking about billions of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 123212.0,
      "end_time": 125921.0,
      "text": "I know this is sobering to think about."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125922.0,
      "end_time": 130280.0,
      "text": "Is this a future we want to leave for our children and grandchildren?"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 130281.0,
      "end_time": 131751.0,
      "text": "I don't think so either."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131752.0,
      "end_time": 133832.0,
      "text": "So let's steer towards a better future."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 133833.0,
      "end_time": 137624.0,
      "text": "Thomas Berry wrote that our great work for our generation"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137625.0,
      "end_time": 141144.0,
      "text": "is to learn to live on the planet at least benignly."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 141145.0,
      "end_time": 143500.0,
      "text": "Why would we do that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143600.0,
      "end_time": 146617.0,
      "text": "One reason we would do that is that our fellow living things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 146618.0,
      "end_time": 148237.0,
      "text": "who happen not to be human,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 148238.0,
      "end_time": 151320.0,
      "text": "don't have a representative in Congress;"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 151330.0,
      "end_time": 153452.0,
      "text": "they don't have a lobbyist in Washington,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153453.0,
      "end_time": 155410.0,
      "text": "they don't have a voice at the table,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155411.0,
      "end_time": 160383.0,
      "text": "and yet, they are completely dependent for their survival on our good will;"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 160384.0,
      "end_time": 162400.0,
      "text": "much like children."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 162694.0,
      "end_time": 167340.0,
      "text": "Let's talk about our country's population and our wildlife."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 167350.0,
      "end_time": 170575.0,
      "text": "We had about five million people in our country around 1800"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 170576.0,
      "end_time": 175476.0,
      "text": "and about 290 million people in 2000 - more now, of course."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 175477.0,
      "end_time": 179523.0,
      "text": "At a conference, I met a scientist, Andrea Laliberte,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 179524.0,
      "end_time": 181216.0,
      "text": "who had done fascinating work"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 181217.0,
      "end_time": 185906.0,
      "text": "comparing wildlife sightings in the 1700 and 1800 in our country"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 185907.0,
      "end_time": 189204.0,
      "text": "to those wildlife range today in our country."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 189205.0,
      "end_time": 193325.0,
      "text": "This chart, the pinkish areas - I'm not sure how it looks here -"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 193326.0,
      "end_time": 196102.0,
      "text": "are where we used to have black bears."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 196103.0,
      "end_time": 198495.0,
      "text": "The yellow areas are where they still are today"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 198496.0,
      "end_time": 201251.0,
      "text": "- you see there's been a lot of recession there."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 201252.0,
      "end_time": 202592.0,
      "text": "This is the gray wolf;"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 202593.0,
      "end_time": 205313.0,
      "text": "we used to have gray wolves running all over our country;"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 205314.0,
      "end_time": 207489.0,
      "text": "- the pinkish areas you see on the chart -"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 207490.0,
      "end_time": 209246.0,
      "text": "not so today."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 209247.0,
      "end_time": 214725.0,
      "text": "We used to have grizzly bears running over about half of our country;"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 214726.0,
      "end_time": 217592.0,
      "text": "as you see, they've receded, and we don't have them."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 217593.0,
      "end_time": 219125.0,
      "text": "This was just 200 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 219126.0,
      "end_time": 220787.0,
      "text": "That yellow island-like area"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 220788.0,
      "end_time": 223437.0,
      "text": "- that would be the Greater Yellowstone ecosystem."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 223438.0,
      "end_time": 227390.0,
      "text": "Let's look at a summary map: take a look at the right here -"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 227400.0,
      "end_time": 231772.0,
      "text": "red is good, green is bad, white is very bad."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 231773.0,
      "end_time": 234740.0,
      "text": "You see that we've lost a lot of species in our country;"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 234741.0,
      "end_time": 238450.0,
      "text": "those white areas mean that all of wildlife that was looked at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 238451.0,
      "end_time": 240690.0,
      "text": "- in this case, in the 1800s -"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 240700.0,
      "end_time": 241410.0,
      "text": "it's gone from our country."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 241411.0,
      "end_time": 243724.0,
      "text": "Do you think is normal not to have wildlife"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 243725.0,
      "end_time": 245885.0,
      "text": "running around us all the time in our country?"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 245886.0,
      "end_time": 247365.0,
      "text": "That's not normal."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 247366.0,
      "end_time": 251890.0,
      "text": "Let's bring it home, here, to the Front Range of Colorado; tonight."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251900.0,
      "end_time": 254328.0,
      "text": "We used to have wild bison; they're gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 254329.0,
      "end_time": 258149.0,
      "text": "We used to have gray wolves; they're gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 258149.0,
      "end_time": 261463.0,
      "text": "We used to have-- - sorry, my clicker's little sluggish -"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261464.0,
      "end_time": 265582.0,
      "text": "grizzly bears; could've been right outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 265583.0,
      "end_time": 267660.0,
      "text": "They're gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 267670.0,
      "end_time": 270702.0,
      "text": "We used to have lynx, the cat; gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 273662.0,
      "end_time": 275800.0,
      "text": "Maybe they are not leaving."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275810.0,
      "end_time": 276265.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 276266.0,
      "end_time": 278143.0,
      "text": "We used to have black-footed ferret,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 278144.0,
      "end_time": 281466.0,
      "text": "very dependent on prairie dog for their survival; gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 281467.0,
      "end_time": 282594.0,
      "text": "We used to have"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 282596.0,
      "end_time": 285604.0,
      "text": "this beautiful, little bird: the mountain plover; also gone."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 285605.0,
      "end_time": 288103.0,
      "text": "This is sobering information, so what can we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 288104.0,
      "end_time": 290253.0,
      "text": "We can choose a better future."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 290255.0,
      "end_time": 291945.0,
      "text": "Let's apply the empathy"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 291946.0,
      "end_time": 296368.0,
      "text": "that we have for our cats, dogs, and other pets"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 296369.0,
      "end_time": 298953.0,
      "text": "to endangered species like this chimpanzee,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 298954.0,
      "end_time": 300502.0,
      "text": "but all endangered species."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 300503.0,
      "end_time": 303363.0,
      "text": "Let's have fewer children; that's one of the most powerful--"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 303364.0,
      "end_time": 304383.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 304384.0,
      "end_time": 305492.0,
      "text": "- Thank you! -"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 305493.0,
      "end_time": 306893.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 306894.0,
      "end_time": 308639.0,
      "text": "- I didn't expect that response. -"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 308640.0,
      "end_time": 312193.0,
      "text": "That's one of the most powerful things that we can do in the United States;"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 312194.0,
      "end_time": 314850.0,
      "text": "if we want to have kids, great; let's have two."
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 314851.0,
      "end_time": 318260.0,
      "text": "If want to have more than two kids, let's adopt."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 318516.0,
      "end_time": 320360.0,
      "text": "What else can we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 322302.0,
      "end_time": 323609.0,
      "text": "Well, we won't go there."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 323610.0,
      "end_time": 324763.0,
      "text": "So, what else can we do?"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 324764.0,
      "end_time": 329650.0,
      "text": "We can help educate girls and provide economic opportunity to women"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 329660.0,
      "end_time": 330476.0,
      "text": "in developing countries."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 330477.0,
      "end_time": 332169.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 332170.0,
      "end_time": 333225.0,
      "text": "Amen!"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 333226.0,
      "end_time": 337878.0,
      "text": "When we do that, those ladies choose to have to have smaller families,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 337879.0,
      "end_time": 340260.0,
      "text": "and we have more nutrition, more health care,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 340270.0,
      "end_time": 341757.0,
      "text": "more education for their kids,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 341758.0,
      "end_time": 344777.0,
      "text": "and the impact on the global population is huge."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 344778.0,
      "end_time": 346329.0,
      "text": "Finally, what we can do"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 346330.0,
      "end_time": 349145.0,
      "text": "is we can give more to our planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 349147.0,
      "end_time": 351652.0,
      "text": "We can give half of our donations, let's say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 351654.0,
      "end_time": 353679.0,
      "text": "to people and people-related causes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 353680.0,
      "end_time": 355898.0,
      "text": "and half of our donations to the planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 355899.0,
      "end_time": 359559.0,
      "text": "to ocean conservation, to wildlife conservation."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 360201.0,
      "end_time": 364419.0,
      "text": "I want to mention, by the way, that today, we only give about 2 to 5%"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 364420.0,
      "end_time": 368992.0,
      "text": "of all giving that goes to environment and wildlife as a category."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 368993.0,
      "end_time": 372275.0,
      "text": "You've been very patient with sometimes, a difficult topic;"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 372276.0,
      "end_time": 374923.0,
      "text": "I just want to say that the thing to think about"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 374924.0,
      "end_time": 378157.0,
      "text": "is do we change, as a species, what do we do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 378159.0,
      "end_time": 381111.0,
      "text": "so that our fellow living beings who happen not to be human"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 381113.0,
      "end_time": 382959.0,
      "text": "can thrive alongside of us"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 382960.0,
      "end_time": 386236.0,
      "text": "a 100, 500, and 1,000 years from now."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 386237.0,
      "end_time": 387605.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 387606.0,
      "end_time": 389320.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}